node.text:
In episode 3 of of my 'How To' series, I'm showing you exactly how to set up and use a resistance band! 😄

There are so many types of resistance bands that can be used for many different exercises, but I want to show you how you can attach longer resistance bands to a bar to help you with things like assisted pull-ups and chin-ups!

You will usually find resistance bands hanging up around the gym, or you can bring your own to ensure you've got the right size available for you. ✔️

The key thing to remember with resistance bands is that the THICKER bands have MORE resistance than the thinner bands. In the case of a pull-up or chin up, the thicker band will assist you more (as there is more resistance) making it easier for you to pull yourself up to complete the exercise.

However, in most other cases (like resistance band tricep extensions or bicep curls) the thinner resistance bands actually make the exercise easier than the thicker ones! And if this confuses you a little bit, don't worry! You will instantly feel the difference and know which one is right to use when you try them out. 😅

I hope this video gives you the confidence to try an assisted pull-up or chin-up next time you are in the gym! I have included these in my new High Intensity Strength Program, which you can try by downloading @Sweat today! 

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatApp #SweatCommunity #gym #gymworkout

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text:
Episode ✌️ of my 'How To' series is all about how to use the Cable & Pulley machine! 
This machine can look quite intimidating at first because there are so many parts to it. I've heard my clients say that they used to walk up to the machine and use whatever attachment is already there because they are too scared (or don't know how) to change them... which I totally understand.

Hopefully, this video will help you gain the confidence to firstly... use this machine, and secondly... use the machine exactly the way you want to! So next time you're in the gym, take me with you and give yourself the time to learn how these parts actually work. I promise it's easier than you have imagined! 😊

My High Intensity Strength program includes the use of this machine, and the @Sweat app will tell you exactly which attachment you need to complete the exercise which should help you build confidence, too! You can try my new gym program today via the link in my bio 😊

PS. All the videos that I will be sharing over the next week have been filmed before Adelaide's current lockdown. Stay safe ❤️

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #Workout #Gym #gymworkout 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text:
INTRODUCING MY NEW 'HOW TO' SERIES - GYM EDITION 🌟
As gyms begin to re-open around the world, I want everyone to feel confident and comfortable getting back to their gym-based workouts.

I also know a lot of women feel intimidated about going to the gym, especially when it comes to using large equipment... so it's for these reasons I want to show you exactly HOW TO navigate a gym setting. In this series, I'll be taking you the step-by-step process as to how to set up and use different equipment around the gym.

To kick the series off, we're starting with the equipment that was requested most by YOU, #SWKCommunity...  THE LEG PRESS! 

We have a variety of gym-based programs in the @Sweat app that involves using the Leg Press, including my new and improved High-Intensity Strength program. So, next time you're in the gym... I want you to take me with you and allow yourself the time to get comfortable with using these bigger machines. Before you know it, you'll wish you stopped avoiding them sooner! 

I hope by the end of this episode you feel a lot LESS intimidated and a lot MORE empowered to use this machine in your training. 

If you're keen to start using the Leg Press in your workouts, I recommend trying my new and improved High Intensity Strength program. It uses larger machines, free weights and bodyweight exercises to help women get fitter and get stronger! You can try it today for free using @Sweat's 7-Day free trial (link in bio)!

It has been great to bring you even more new gym programs to Sweat and from now on we will be working with @iFIT to help deliver even more choice and variety to you all!

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #LegPress #gym #gymequipment #gymtutorial

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text: Let’s do this!! Take me anywhere with you and let’s train abs together !! (No equipment) EXPRESS WORKOUT

"But Kayla, I don't have time to workout today!!" 
... are you sure about that?! 🤣🤣

If this sounds like you, I'm here to tell you that there is almost ALWAYS time to squeeze in a workout! You just have to start telling yourself that any amount of time working out it's worth it! 
 
I've created this 5-minute "follow-along" lower body workout that should have you breaking a sweat and feeling accomplished in a short amount of time! I'm ready to work out with you right now, but it's up to YOU to set aside the time to get your body moving today! 

✅ Squat Pulse - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Curtsey Lunge - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Glute Bridge Walkout - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

 Do 3 laps

✅ Squat Pulse finisher - 30 secs

I certainly felt the burn after that!! Did you? 🔥😅

If you love the thought of an express workout - there are SO many incredible programs in the @Sweat app that are ready and waiting for you! Head to the link in my bio for a 7-Day free trial and get moving today!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatwithKayla 

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatwithKayla #SweatCommunity #ExpressWorkout #Workout

node.text:
Are your glute bridges actually working your glutes? Or just hurting your lower back? 🤔
Glute bridges are one of those exercises that look quite easy to do... but they can hurt the wrong muscles if done incorrectly! 

I've noticed that some people push their hips as high as they can, causing them to over-extend and put pressure on their lower back. If this sounds like you, or you haven't been feeling the burn in your glutes when doing glute bridges, I want you to watch this video and practice my number one tip! 

You should absolutely be feeling your glutes burn if you do this! 🔥
Let me know if this has helped you!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

This is an easy one to get wrong ❌ 
So if you do Ab Bikes often, I want you to take the time to learn how to get them right! ✅

In this video, I break down the exercise into smaller steps to help you perfect your form. Once you've mastered each movement, add each step in until you build up to a full Ab Bike! 

Here are some do's and don'ts to remember:
DO
✅Rest hands in front of ears
✅Rotate at the torso
✅Bring knees in close to the chest
✅Extend your legs in a push and pull motion
✅Elevate your shoulders

DON'T
❌Pull your neck up with your hands behind your head
❌Do small in and out motions with your legs
❌Curve your back away from the floor

What other exercises do you want to learn from me? Comment below!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatwithKayla

#SWK #SWKcommunity #Exercises #BBG #SweatwithKayla

Right, so today I'm going to break down the burpee for you to make it easier.

It's still not going to be EASY (it's a burpee haha!!)... but these tips will make it easier to do 😅⁣ You're still going to #SweatwithKayla and you'll find burpees in my High Intensity program. There's a link in my bio for a 7 day FREE trial of the @Sweat app. 

Follow this and see how it feels:
✅Start at the top of your mat
✅Put your hands down in front of your feet as you squat down
✅Jump back into a push up position
✅Make sure your wrist and shoulder is in line
✅Back nice and straight
✅Make sure you're stable and have a strong core 
✅Jump back in with feet apart (not together!)
✅Stand up and do your jump
✅Find your rhythm

Some common mistakes:
❌Starting with your hands too far in front of you 
❌Not holding your core tight throughout each movement
❌Letting your back dip down into an unstable position
❌Jumping in too far with your feet and putting pressure on your knees
❌Arching your back too much before jumping to a standing position

Now, I've shown you the correct technique how do your burpees feel?

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SweatwithKayla #SWKcommunity #Sweat #Sweatcommunity #fitness #burpee

node.text:
For a lot of women around the world, the last 12 months have been tough. For many of you it meant an adjustment to working out at home, or perhaps, it meant losing the time, space or motivation to work out all together. I want you to know that you’re not alone in facing these challenges. We see you and and at @Sweat we want to help.

I want to introduce you to Sweat’s new MOVE AGAIN programs, designed specifically for those who have had a break in their fitness journey due to the pandemic.

These four new beginner level programs consist of two 20-minute workouts a week for four weeks and are led by four inspiring trainers that are dedicated to help you form healthy habits and get you back into fitness. 

👉 Bodyweight Strength with Anissia (@avh__fitness)
🌟 When Anissia isn’t playing basketball, she’s all about strength and bodyweight circuits. Her approach to fitness is all about getting back to basics and her Bodyweight Strength workouts require absolutely no equipment.

👉 Low Impact HIIT with Samantha (@so_manti)
🌟 With Samantha you can expect a fast-paced and upbeat style to her Low Impact HIIT workouts which are perfect for getting a quick sweat up in a short amount of time.

👉 Strength & Cardio with Marilyn (@fitwithmarilyn)
🌟 Marilyn’s approach to fitness is about maximising your time with fun and dynamic workouts to help you build form and to find your love for moving again. You’ll feel strong off the back of these workouts and the combination of rep based strength and timed based cardio.

👉 Low Impact Strength with Kelsey (@kelseywells)
🌟 Now Kelsey is one of my best friends and she has been part of the Sweat family for a while now and we so are excited to be adding a low-impact strength program. Kelsey’s new dumbbell based workouts are great to build your confidence using weights and will have you feeling strong again in no time.

We’ve designed each program to support your physical and mental health. We want you to remember how good it feels to move again!

So why not take advantage of our Sweat 7-day free trial and start moving again

www.kaylaitsines.com/moveagain

#MoveAgain #Sweat #Sweatcommunity #SWKcommunity #KaylaItsines

I absolutely LOVE doing ab workouts, and clearly many of you ladies in the #SweatCommunity feel the same way because they are my most requested workouts! ⁣😍
⁣
This Advanced Ab Follow Along uses ZERO equipment and will put most people through their paces. 5 minutes of 5 exercises with a rest in-between each, let's do this! 

✅ Single-Arm and Leg Jackknife - 45 sec
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ Straight-Leg Raise & Hip Lift - 45 sec
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ Bent Leg Toe Taps - 45 sec 
✅ Rest - 15 sec

node.text:
I wanted to give you an overview about my programs on @sweat so you can decide which one is right for you!
Their names may have changed but why I designed them and what you can get out of them HASN'T. 

I believe I have a program for EVERYONE, you just need to find one that suits YOU! 👇

👉 HIGH INTENSITY WITH KAYLA (formerly BBG)
✅ High intensity 28 minute workouts. This is my original and most well known program, completed by thousands of women like you all around the world! It has been designed to help women achieve their fitness goals with short and very effective workouts. This is THE program to become fitter, stronger and more confident!
 
👉 HIGH INTENSITY ZERO EQUIPMENT WITH KAYLA (formerly BBG Zero Equipment) 
✅ All workouts in this program are similar to my High Intensity program, but they require ZERO equipment so you can do them anytime, anywhere! The workouts are all less than 28 minutes. All you need is YOU!!.... and some water haha.

👉 HIGH INTENSITY STRENGTH⁣ WITH KAYLA (formerly BBG Stronger)
✅ I designed this program to help women to feel confident and comfortable in the gym and around big gym equipment. My program allows you to get the most out of your time at the gym with easy to follow structured workouts that build from beginner through to advanced. 
⁣
👉 LOW IMPACT WITH KAYLA
✅ #LowImpactwithKayla This is my NO JUMPING PROGRAM and is for all women no matter what your age or fitness level. It's perfect if you're just starting out, or are returning to fitness after injury or a break. The workouts are low intensity and can all be done in under 30 minutes

✅ #PostPregnancy I created this program to support women who are looking to regain their strength and fitness after pregnancy and birth. The workouts include low-impact exercises and short - ranging from 15 to 25 minutes. Please ensure you have clearance from your healthcare professional

If you're just starting out, if you’re new to @sweat, or if you’re looking for a new challenge, you can train with me! Download Sweat now and take advantage of our 7-day free trial and give my programs a go. 💪⁣

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SweatwithKayla #SWKcommunity #Sweatcommunity

node.title: Which of my programs is right for you?

#SWEATCHALLENGE LADIES, YOU DID IT! 🎉 You finished the 6-week Sweat Challenge 🙌😍 I am SO proud! 

It is honestly so amazing to see so many women across this incredible community coming together like this! 

Congratulations to everyone that committed to this Challenge and stuck with it to the very end. I hope you feel accomplished and determined to keep building on your achievements from the past 6-weeks. 🔥❤️

Now if you're wondering where to next.... don't worry, there are SO many programs in the @Sweat app that will help you to keep progressing on your fitness journey.
If you have been doing my programs during this Challenge, here are some suggestions on where you can go next👇

If you did ....

High Intensity Challenge 👉 My High Intensity Program OR High Intensity Strength 

High Intensity Zero Equipment Challenge 👉 High Intensity Zero Equipment Program 

Low Impact Challenge Challenge 👉 Low Impact Program 

There are also so many other incredible programs in the @Sweat app from our other trainers which may be suitable for you! Just open the app and follow the prompts to check out all of the available programs! 😊

Again, CONGRATULATIONS LADIES. You should be so, so proud!!! 😍

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatChallenge #workout #fitness 

www.KaylaItsines.com/SweatWithKayla

node.text:
MY POST-PREGNANCY PROGRAM 👩‍🍼🍼
Recently had a baby and thinking about doing my Post Pregnancy program‍? 😊 Here's what you can expect!

This program is suitable for anyone who has had a baby and wants to rebuild their fitness. It has been designed by me, alongside a team of exercise scientists for women, to help them return to exercise with confidence.

The program can support new mothers to rebuild their strength and fitness after pregnancy and birth. The workouts are short, ranging from 15-25 minutes, to fit into the busy life of a new mother!

Every woman's post-pregnancy journey is different, so it’s essential that you work closely with your health professionals and only do exercise that you have clearance to do. 
For the ladies wondering, I also had a cesarean so I factored this into my programming too for any mum who is like me! 

As a new mother, making time to look after yourself and keep a healthy mindset is so important! It can be hard to take time away from looking after your new baby, and that’s why I designed this program to be flexible, with workouts you can do at home.

If you’re ready to give my Post Pregnancy program a go and you don’t already have @Sweat, download the app via the link in my bio today!

#SweatwithKayla #SWKcommunity #PostPregnancy #PostPregnancyWorkout #PostPartum

www.kaylaitsines.com/PostPregnancyWithKayla

HAPPY WORLD AVOCADO DAY!! 🥑🥑
I love that there is an official day to celebrate and eat avocados 🤣

If I ever ask Arna what she wants to eat, she has been saying “Avocado!!”, so I have been making lots of smashed avocado on cut up pieces of toast 😝 definitely not as fancy as this picture though! 

Some of my favourite ways that you can use avocados are:

🥑 Smashed Avo & Eggs on Toast 
🥑 Guacamole & Corn Chips

I’ve also heard that avocado chocolate mousse is apparently delicious but I’m can't say I'm sure about that one 🙃🤣... sounds like my sisters vibe ...not for me. 

I want to hear how you eat your avocado #SWKCommunity on this World Avocado Day! Let me know below!

I LOVE hearing from members who have been here since the eBook days!! 🤣❤️ Emily (@not_another_fitmom), it’s so awesome to hear about how far you’ve come on your fitness journey, and about all the @Sweat programs you’ve completed along the way! 

Some words from Emily: “I started @kayla_itsines ebook 5 years ago! I’d already been working out for a little while. When I started following her on IG and saw all the amazing transformation pics, I was hooked. I wanted to look and feel strong like all of those incredible ladies. 

When I first started I had two boys under three 🤪❤️ I would workout in the basement after they went to bed. I had 2 different size weights and a mat, that’s it. 💪🏻 But I was determined! I’ve come a long way since then, and a lot has changed. I had another baby boy, we moved, I became a CPT, and I downloaded the Sweat app. 

I’ve done BBG, BBG stronger, Post Pregnancy PWR, PWR, PWR at home, and now I’m following @Cassolholm program for the challenge. Please remember that we all start somewhere. Never compare your day with someone’s day 1,754. 💪🏻💯❤️”

AMAZING effort Emily!! You too can get started by downloading the Sweat app today! Just head to the link in my bio 💪

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #SWK #SweatCommunity #Progress #Fitness

node.text:
Daydreaming about a tropical holiday right about now in this freezing Adelaide weather! I can’t wait to be able to travel overseas again 🙌

I would get a fresh fruit platter every morning when I was in Bali, with lots of watermelon, pineapple, mango, and dragonfruit! It can also be called pitaya depending on where you are from, and it’s either white or this very beautiful vibrant pink 😍 it kind of tasted like nothing until I squeezed the lime juice over the top, and then wow, it was amazing!! 

I actually ordered this fruit platter for Arna, thinking it would be a few small pieces of fruit she could have . . . and then they brought this out!! 🤣 I was like uhh, this is way too pretty for a 1 year old 😝

It's so important to have fresh fruit as part of a balanced, healthy diet! You can make little changes to your meals to include servings of fruit, like topping your breakfast oats with fresh apple or banana, or having some yoghurt and blueberries for an after dinner sweet treat. I think it's definitely easier to eat more fruit in the summer time - it's so refreshing in the hot weather 🤩

For now, I think I’ll have to settle for eating my fruit in this cold, rainy weather, and just pretend that I’m by the pool in Bali 🤣 

#SweatCommunity #Food #SweatwithKayla #Swk #SWKCommunity #Fruit #food #Travel

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by KAYLA ITSINES on July 29, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The day you plant the seed is not the day you eat the fruit.'.

node.text:
If you planted a seed in your garden, you wouldn’t wake up the next morning expecting a beautiful, big tree to suddenly appear, would you? You know that the seed needs water, sun, and lots and lots of time to grow!

It’s the exact same way you should approach your own fitness journey. It takes a balance of commitment, effort, and patience. It’s showing up every day, and putting in that hard work to get to your goal. 

As much as we wish for things to happen overnight, it does take time for growth to happen! I know that it can definitely be frustrating at times - I think back to when I had just had Arna, and was slowly starting to work out again. I felt like a beginner starting a fresh, and all I wanted was to snap my fingers and be back at my original fitness level! 
I knew it would take patience and hard work, and I would get to that stage again. Slowly but surely, I built up my strength and endurance, and now I feel just as strong as ever!

You need to allow time for progress to happen, and you will grow in other ways on the journey too!

Plant your seed, give it some care, and watch it grow into something amazing ❤️

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Motivation #Quote

MUST READ THIS CAPTION! 
From member Kate (@mama_4_fit_journey) today! 🙌 Not only are you looking so STRONG, but your confidence is absolutely shining through your smile 😍 (... and your cat looks kind of nice, too 🤣)! I’m so glad that you have enjoyed doing not only my programs, but also that you have found the support of the amazing women in the #SweatCommunity!

Here are some words from Kate: “Today I couldn’t help but try out @kayla_itsines new program! And it did not disappoint! No one can make me #Sweat quite like Kayla can!! And I was dripping in sweat by the end of the first triset!

. . . I began @Sweat because of Kayla, I had followed her for years and she is who made me first start believing in myself! She had built this community full of women who built one another up, who truly believed in women empowering other women!
I am glad I took that step and finally joined the #SweatCommunity because this community has been even more amazing then I could have ever imagined!!

I fell in love with Kayla’s program and then fell in love with her zero equipment program!! There are times where i want to go back to her program just because I feel as if I owe so much to her, she helped me fall in love with myself! She taught me that my strength is beautiful! That showing my kids that loving yourself and showing your body love is so very important! That taking that time for me is okay! That my fitness journey is so much more of a mental journey then I could have ever imagined!

So today on this thankful Thursday I am thankful to the woman who started this all!! I am thankful to all the other trainers who have supported all of us through our journeys!! What a beautiful community this is!!

. . . So proud of how far I have come! And cannot wait to see where I will go!”

I love this attitude so much!! I can’t wait to see what you achieve next Kate! 💪 If you want to get started with my programs, head to the link in my bio and download @Sweat today! 

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #SweatCommunity #Progress #Fitness #SWKCommunity 

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

WEEK 6 CHALLENGE ME WORKOUT - GYM VERSION 💪 🙌 The final week of the Challenge is HERE ladies, and we are going to smash it! 🤩 For those of you lucky enough to have access to a gym, here is the FINAL ‘Challenge Me’ full body workout for the Challenge! 

If you have been loving these gym workouts, I’ve just launched my new and improved High Intensity Strength program with a brand new format, which has been revamped and is perfect for completing in the gym 🙌

You’ll need the following equipment for this gym workout:

👉 Dumbbells
👉 Skipping Rope
👉 Bench
👉 Deadball
👉 Cable

Circuit 1:
✅ Double-Pulse Jump Lunge - 24 reps (12 per side)
✅ Skipping - 30 sec
✅ Alternating Bench Press - 16 repss (8 per side)
✅ Deadball Slam - 10 reps

Circuit 2:
✅ Front Lateral Pull - 24 (12 per side)
✅ X Mountain Climber - 24 (12 per side)
✅ Burpee and Shoulder Press - 8 reps
✅ Lateral Shoot Through - 24 reps (12 per side)

Let’s finish this challenge off strong ladies! 💪 I want to hear how you have all gone with the challenge! Comment below and let me know how you went!

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

#SweatwithKayla #SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #Workout

node.text:
WARNING. DO NOT BE FOOLED BY THIS ADORABLE FACE. 
8 things my toddler threw a tantrum about recently..... 😊😊😊😊😊😊😊

1. I didn't let her put her hand in the blender when I was making muffins - tantrum.

2. She didn't like her breakfast & threw it on the floor. Then was upset that it was on the floor. tantrum.

3. I wouldn't let her hold a very long and very sharp sashimi knife. tantrum.

4. She decided, just on this one occasion, that she HATES bubbles in her bathtub. tantrum.

5. She wanted Ace (my husky) to go outside because he was wet and when he didn't go outside she told me that Ace bit her hand off, when I was watching them the whole time and literally nothing happened (and she still had both hands haha). tantrum.

6. She thought my sister's dog Reggie was going to steal her sock (he was sitting near it) so she smacked him said "DATS MYYYY SOCKKKK NOOOOOO" and then.... tantrum.

7. I wouldn't let her drink my greek coffee. tantrum. 

8. and now she HAS to drink water out of a tiny greek coffee cup (aka "a big girl cup"), or else.... tantrum.

and the list goes on....

There must be a reason they look so adorable in their terrible two's - to balance out their behavior 🤣🤣❤️

Safe to say I've had my work cut out for me hahah! #SWKCommunity mums - tell me what the funniest tantrum your kids have had.

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #mum #mumlife #toddlers

node.text:
In episode 3 of of my 'How To' series, I'm showing you exactly how to set up and use a resistance band! 😄

There are so many types of resistance bands that can be used for many different exercises, but I want to show you how you can attach longer resistance bands to a bar to help you with things like assisted pull-ups and chin-ups!

You will usually find resistance bands hanging up around the gym, or you can bring your own to ensure you've got the right size available for you. ✔️

The key thing to remember with resistance bands is that the THICKER bands have MORE resistance than the thinner bands. In the case of a pull-up or chin up, the thicker band will assist you more (as there is more resistance) making it easier for you to pull yourself up to complete the exercise.

However, in most other cases (like resistance band tricep extensions or bicep curls) the thinner resistance bands actually make the exercise easier than the thicker ones! And if this confuses you a little bit, don't worry! You will instantly feel the difference and know which one is right to use when you try them out. 😅

I hope this video gives you the confidence to try an assisted pull-up or chin-up next time you are in the gym! I have included these in my new High Intensity Strength Program, which you can try by downloading @Sweat today!
